OL,3,GNorth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FCloudy at first this morning
OL,6,Fwith frequent scattered showers on a
OL,7,Fbrisk wind. Some brighter spells will
OL,8,Fdevelop through the day and showers
OL,9,Fwill become less frequent. Feeling
OL,10,Fpleasant in the sunny spells.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FShowers will ease away
OL,13,Ftonight, allowing it to become dry and
OL,14,Fclear across the region. Turning
OL,15,Fchilly under the clear skies with a
OL,16,Ffew mist and fog patches possible.
OL,17,
OL,18,CSunday:FAny mist or fog will quickly
OL,19,Fclear in the morning. Staying dry with
OL,20,Fsunny spells at first, but cloud
OL,21,Flikely increasing during the afternoon.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
